## Test Anti-Pattern Audit: `ProductCatalogTests.cs`

### Summary

| Severity | Count |
|----------|-------|
| **Critical** | 2 (systemic — affects all 10 tests) |
| **Medium** | 1 |

This is a textbook **coverage-touching** test class. All 10 public methods of `ProductCatalog` are invoked (yielding ~95% line coverage), but nearly zero behavioral outcomes are verified. These tests will pass even if every method is reimplemented to do nothing.

---

### Critical Findings

#### 1. Coverage Touching (Systemic)

The class methodically calls every public method on `ProductCatalog` — in near-declaration order — without asserting meaningful outcomes. The structure is uniform: arrange a product, call the method, move on.

**Impact:** Bugs in `UpdatePrice`, `ApplyBulkDiscount`, `RemoveProduct`, `ImportFromCsv`, and `GetProductCount` will never be caught by these tests despite the code being "covered."

---

#### 2. No Assertions / Trivial Assertions (per-method breakdown)

| Test Method | Problem | Bug it would miss |
|---|---|---|
| `AddProduct_Works` (line 17) | Zero assertions | `Save()` silently drops the product |
| `UpdatePrice_Works` (line 31) | Zero assertions | Price never actually changes |
| `RemoveProduct_Works` (line 39) | Zero assertions | Product remains in store |
| `GetProductCount_Works` (line 63) | Zero assertions | Count returns wrong number |
| `ApplyBulkDiscount_Works` (line 68) | Zero assertions | Discount math is wrong (e.g., `* fraction` instead of `* (1 - fraction)`) |
| `ImportFromCsv_Works` (line 85) | Zero assertions | Parsing fails silently or stores garbage |
| `GetProduct_Works` (line 23) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only | Returns wrong SKU/Name/Price — test still passes |
| `SearchProducts_Works` (line 46) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only | Returns empty list or wrong products — test still passes |
| `GetAllProducts_Works` (line 55) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only | Returns empty list — test still passes |
| `ExportToCsv_Works` (line 77) | `Assert.IsNotNull` only | CSV is malformed — test still passes |

**Concrete fixes:**

```csharp
// BEFORE — AddProduct_Works (line 17)
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_Works()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);
}

// AFTER
[TestMethod]
public void AddProduct_StoresProductRetrievableBySku()
{
    var product = new Product("SKU-001", "Widget", 9.99m);
    _catalog.AddProduct(product);

    var stored = _catalog.GetProduct("SKU-001");
    Assert.AreEqual("Widget", stored?.Name);
    Assert.AreEqual(9.99m, stored?.Price);
}
```

